					Full Description



AMC Entertainment Holdings, Inc., incorporated on June 6, 2007, is a holding company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, including AMC Entertainment Inc. (AMCE), American Multi-Cinema, Inc. (OpCo) and its subsidiaries, is engaged in the theatrical exhibition business. The Company operates through theatrical exhibition operations segment. The Company operates over 900 theatres with approximately 10,000 screens globally, including over 661 theatres with approximately 8,200 screens in the United States and over 244 theatres with approximately 2,200 screens in Europe. Its subsidiary also includes Carmike Cinemas, Inc. The Company licenses first-run motion pictures from distributors owned by film production companies and from independent distributors. It licenses films on a film-by-film and theatre-by-theatre basis. The Company also offers a range of food and beverage items, which include popcorn; soft drinks; candy; hot dogs; specialty drinks, including beers, wine and mixed drinks, and made to order hot foods, including menu choices, such as curly fries, chicken tenders and mozzarella sticks. As of December 31, 2015, the Company had implemented dine-in theatre concepts at 19 locations, which feature kitchen facilities, seat-side servers, and a separate bar and lounge area. Its theatrical exhibition circuit is located in California, Texas, New Jersey, Arizona, Michigan, Massachusetts, Pennsylvania, Maryland, Minnesota, North Carolina, District of Columbia, Nevada, South Carolina and the United Kingdom, among others.

» Full Overview of AMC







